  "guidebook.chapter.Title.NewMechanics": "[center][font=dialogue]New Mechanics[/font][/center]
[font=dialogue]Dual Wielding[/font]
Sword & Sorcery introduces a dual-wielding feature, allowing you to attack with two weapons at once. To equip a weapon in your off-hand slot, open your inventory and click a button to the left of the window that looks like the following:
 
[image=spacechase0.SpaceCore/ExtraEquipmentIcon]
After that, you should see a slot labelled [color=black]Offhand[/color]. Place your desired secondary weapon in that slot. Now, whenever you swing your weapon or use your weapon ability in your hotbar, both will be used.
 
[font=dialogue]Armor[/font]
[if=PLAYER_HAS_SEEN_EVENT Current SnS.Ch1.Mateo.18]
After reaching level 1 [link=NEA/ArtificerSkill]Artificer[/link], you can craft armor for the armor slot on the equipment menu (this is the same menu with the dual wielding offhand slot, explained in the last section). Armor acts as an extra buffer that absorbs damage before your health bar. It automatically repairs itself at the beginning of each day.
[/if]
[else](locked)[/else]
 
[font=dialogue]Adventure Bar[/font]
[if=PLAYER_HAS_MAIL Current SnS_AdventureBar]
On the left side of your screen, you can see two columns with a bar underneath. This is the Adventure Bar. The columns repesent ability slots that you can activate with keybindings. The bar underneath is your Aether, which is consumed to use most abilities. To use an ability, use the keybinding configured for that slot. (default: Ctrl+NUMBER or Shift+NUMBER, though these can be configured in GMCM). If you're using a gamepad, the [link=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/25257]Radial Menu[/link] mod can also be used to trigger configured abilities.
 
You can change what abilities are in which slots by using the Adventure Bar Menu keybinding (default: U). You will unlock different abilities throughout the story of the Sword & Sorcery.
 
The adventure bar can be hidden with the configured keybinding (default: Ctrl+U).
[/if]
[else](locked)[/else]
 
