"guidebook.chapter.TOP.AlchemyTransmutation": "[center][font=dialogue]Alchemy & Transmutation[/font][/center]
 
[font=dialogue]Alchemy[/font]
Upon unlocking Sorcery, you will also gain the ability to learn how to make alchemical potions via the Philosopher's Stone menu. Like spells, these recipes are learned by exchanging [link=TOP/ElementalEssences]Elemental Essences[/link] in via sorcery research in the Magical Grimoire.
 
All potions apply buffs that last for 11 minutes and 40 seconds.
 
>Verdant - Tastes weirdly like the potion The Wizard gave you... +5 Foraging
>Scarlet - Let the hate flow through you. +5 Attack
>Heather - Zoom, zoom, zoom! +5 Speed
>Zydrate - Comes in a little glass vial. +3 Speed, Def, Attack
>Pistachio - Helps you feel very inspired to get farmwork done! +5 farming
>Dahlia - Almost as pretty in color as the flower it's made from. +1 farming, fishing mining
>Slushie - Wow! All that sugar makes for great energy. +10 max stamina
>Matrix - Perfect for a day in the mines. +5 mining, +3 magnetic radius
>McDougal - The luckiest thing you'll ever drink. +5 Luck
>Toirneach - For those tricky combat scenarios. +4 Mining, +4 def
 
[font=dialogue]Transmutation[/font]
If you find yourself in need of a specific [link=TOP/ElementalEssences]Elemental Essences[/link], you can transmutate one essence into another from the Transmutation menu in your Magical Grimoire.
 
The conversation ratio for essences is 1:1 and will pull from the first available essence in your inventory.",

